article.headline: North Dakota 78, Dickinson St. 48
article.story: North Dakota bounced back from a 29-point loss to rival North Dakota State with a 78-48 victory over NAIA opponent Dickinson State on Friday night. North Dakota's defense was impressive in the first half, leading 33-13 at the break. In the second half, it put up 45 points. Four players finished in double figures, with Jaron Nash and Terrel de Rouen leading the way with 13 apiece. North Dakota shot a season-high 57.1 percent after being held to 33.3 against the Bison last Saturday.
